            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> After commit bec13cf, line2byte never returns -1 even the buffer is empty. \r\n\r\nThis was an intentional change. `line2byte(1)` never consistently returned -1 when the buffer is empty, only when it is unloaded. Quoting the documentation\r\n\r\n> When {lnum} is invalid -1 is returned\r\n\r\n\"1\" is a valid line buffer even in an completely empty buffer, as long as it is loaded.",
